{
  "doc_id": "28356",
  "text": "MSPR is a member of the MET protooncogene family of RTKs that mediates multiple signaling cascades impacting cell motility, adhesion, proliferation, and apoptosis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . MSPR is expressed in multiple epithelial cancer cell types: non-small cell lung cancer, hepatocellular carcinomas, pancreatic cancers, and squamous cell carcinomas [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . We found no reports in the literature of MSPR expression in melanoma cells. However, we discovered that MSPR was activated in every melanoma cell line and tumor using the RTK arrays. The ligand for MSPR is MSP (hepatocyte growth factor-like protein).",
